Orange Democratic Movement party on Friday conducted party primaries for party members and aspirants in two counties, Nairobi and Mombasa for different positions. In Nairobi, primaries were conducted for Members of Parliament in Westlands, Lang'ata and Kibra constituencies. All County Assembly wards also held the primaries apart from Upper Savannah, Kayole North, Waithaka, Kayole Central, Kayole Area 2, Dandora Area 1, Pipeline, Mowlew, Kahawa West, Zimmerman and Ngara wards. The nominations that were set to take place in Siaya County on Friday for Gem Constituency were postponed until further notice. NEB notified all the party members who are yet to receive their nominations certificates, to call its office from Monday 25, for guidance on the date and time that the certificates will be issued to them which will be done by the county.